&quot;One problem I can see already is that some seem to be under the impression there are only four factions -- neutral, evil, good, and Iksar. I see about eight: alignment-based evil, alignment-based good, philosophical evil, philosophical good, self-serving neutral, indifferent neutral, Iksar loyalist, and Iksar exile. None of these really get along with each other, and all of them have their own culture that's laid atop that of their basic race, class, and deity&quot;.<br>
<br>
I agree completely on this one. The Necropolis, for instance, I think would fall under alignment evil. Mycharacter would be more philosophical evil. She definately has her own way of doing things, and even though I RP her as evil, she has been labled a &quot;Lightbringer&quot; IC'ly, by the leader of the Necropolis, Shintou for the fact that some of her friends, which she considers neutral, are looked at as goodby the old traditional standards. As such, because I am Guild Leader, my guild is labeld &quot;lightbringer&quot; by him and those of the Necropolis as well.<br>
<br>
To me, the char is evil depending on how they RP, not from which culture they spring from. There is a Koda'Dal out there, that has a Teir'Dal soul, and memories of her past life as a Teir'Dal. Does this make her evil? She is closer to that than good, for sure. Granted, this is also a rather a young character.<br>
<br>
Mayhap a 'subculture' is also needed ... another organization like the Necropolis, but one with less restrictive views on what is percieved as evil. Where those who traditionally would be deemed good, but RP evil, are welcomed. Say for instance, a wood elf druid, that RP's unkempt. Or a druid of Karana, that RP's they follow the Storm Lord for the Power and destructive qualities of the storm.<br>
<br>
The same for the Fellowship. If it is the same Fellowship I knew about when I played a paladin, they will not allow into their ranks any who are 'traditionally considereid evil.&quot; So, the Teir'Dal SK out there that worships Tunare, would be excluded, for his being a Dark Elf. Perhaps another Light / Good organization is needed there, as well. One that would include those traditionally evil, that RP as good.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp.<br>
